E. coli, in pure or mixed culture, was the most frequently isolated microorganism: 109 isolates were recovered from 57 puppies (one isolate from 18 puppies, two isolates from 27 puppies and three isolates from 11 puppies, four isolates from 1 puppy), i.e. mean number of E. coli isolates per puppy was 1.88 ± 0.10 (P
 < 0.001 when comparing mean number of isolates per lamb and per puppy). Other bacteria isolated were Enterobacter spp., Klebsiella spp., Proteus spp. and Streptococcus spp. (Table 2
).
